As soon as I STOPPED

COMPARING myself…the sooner I became a HAPPIER version of ME. A leveled up, more confident, kinder and care free ME.

There’s no secret sauce…but what has helped me is 1. Acknowledging when I’m feeling that way 2. Accepting those feelings and 3. LETTING them go. 🕊️

Tips to be “TONED” 🤫

It sounds simple yet remaining consistent is the real challenge.
And if I believe in you, than you should too🫶🏼🌻💪🏼

1. Swap your carbs for BETTER carbs!
Starchy carbs like pasta, white rice or breads don’t thrive in our digestive system and tend to leave us with empty calories and lack of nutrients. Try adding more fruits and whole grains like oats and brown rice to your meals. Along with healthy fats like avocado, nuts and coconut oil…your body will thank you ◡̈ 

2. Please don’t skip out on WATER.
Our muscles are almost 80% water and dehydration leads to muscle breakdown. Stay hydrated out there💧

3. Incorporate interval training⏱️
Lose fat without sacrificing muscle. Sprint it out or increase your heart rate for a short period of time by hitting 3-4 sets with 20-30 reps of an exercise and embrace that burn baby🔥

4. Protein is the 🐐 to muscle.
I’m sure everyone has heard this a million times. But that’s because it’s crucial to building/maintaining muscle mass during a weight loss phase.

5. Get your R&R in and know that it absolutely will not be easy.
Because then EVERYONE would do it. Find ways to reduce your stress levels so that not so nice fat storing hormone cortisol can get out and stay out🚫👎🏼

Curtsey Lunges

DB Sumo Squats
And Abductions
